ench target shooter (d. 1933) *[[1871]] &ndash; [[Sydney Chapman (economist)|Sydney Chapman]], English economist and civil servant (d. 1951) *[[1875]] &ndash; [[Vladimir Vidrić]], Croatian poet and lawyer (d. 1909) *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Paul Poiret]], French fashion designer (d. 1944) *[[1882]] &ndash; [[Holland Smith]], American general (d. 1967) *[[1884]] &ndash; [[Princess Beatrice of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha]] (d. 1966) * 1884 &ndash; [[Oliver Kirk]], American boxer (d. 1960) * 1884 &ndash; [[Daniel Varoujan]], Armenian poet and educator (d. 1915) *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Albert Jean Amateau]], Turkish rabbi, lawyer, and activist (d. 1996) * 1889 &ndash; [[Prince Erik, Duke of Västmanland]] (d. 1918) * 1889 &ndash; [[Marie-Antoinette de Geuser]], French mystic (d. 1918) * 1889 &ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]], Austrian born German politician, [[Führer]] of [[Nazi Germany]] (d. 1945) * 1889 &ndash; [[Tonny Kessler]], Dutch footballer (d. 1960) *[[1890]] &ndash; [[Maurice Duplessis]], Canadian lawyer and politician, 16th [[Premier of Quebec]] (d. 1959) * 1890 &ndash; [[Adolf Schärf]], Austrian soldier and politician, 6th [[President of Austria]] (d. 1965) *[[1891]] &ndash; [[Dave Bancroft]], American baseball player and manager (d. 1972) *[[1893]] &ndash; [[Harold Lloyd]], American actor, comedian, and producer (d. 1971) * 1893 &ndash; [[Joan Miró]], Spanish painter and sculptor (d. 1983) *[[1895]] &ndash; [[Emile Christian]], American trombonist and composer (d. 1973) * 1895 &ndash; [[Henry de Montherlant]], French essayist, novelist, and dramatist (d. 1972) *[[1896]] &ndash; [[Wop May]], Canadian captain and pilot (d. 1952) *[[1899]] &ndash; [[Alan Arnett McLeod]], Canadian lieutenant, [[Victoria Cross]] recipient (d. 1918) *[[1904]] &ndash; [[Bruce Cabot]], American actor (d. 1972) *[[1907]] &ndash; [[Miran Bux]], Pakistani cricketer (d. 1991) * 1907 &ndash; [[Augoustinos Kantiotes]], Greek bishop (d. 2010) *[[1908]] &ndash; [[Lionel Hampton]], African-American vibraphone player