'''Boe-OFT''' (Boeing Orbital Flight Test) is the first orbital mission of the [[Boeing CST-100 Starliner]]. It is an uncrewed flight test.
== Mission == The first [[United Launch Alliance]] [[Atlas V]] N22 rocket, designated AV-080, will launch the CST-100 Starliner spacecraft on an unpiloted Orbital Test Flight (OFT) to the [[International Space Station]]. The capsule will dock with the space station, then return to Earth to land in the Western United States after an orbital shakedown cruise ahead of [[Boe-CFT]].
