{{Refimprove|date=March 2008}} {{Infobox recurring event | image = Borderfest mascot.jpg | imagesize = frameless | caption = Borderfest mascot at Borderfest 2008 | begins = | ends = | date = | frequency = annual | location = [[Hidalgo, Texas]] | first = 1975 | last = | participants = | footnotes = }}
'''Borderfest''' is an Annual Festival held in [[Hidalgo, Texas|Hidalgo]], [[Texas]]. The first Borderfest ever held was in 1976. It is the largest and oldest music festival in [[South Texas]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myborderfest.com/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-03-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140208042856/http://www.myborderfest.com/ |archivedate=2014-02-08 |df= }}{{rs|date=June 2014}}</ref> and includes a variety of foods and cultures from around the world.
==History== Borderfest started in 1976 as a committee of the Hidalgo Chamber of Commerce to promote cultural, international and community spirit. The initial event was a small community festival lasting one day and drawing some 500 people. Today, the festival has grown.
Annually the festival Donates $40,000 to $50,000 for local scholarships.[http://www.borderfest.org/06%20site/history.html]{{dead link|date=July 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}
== Mission == Borderfest’s mission is dedicated to cultural enrichment, arts education and heritage preservation in South Texas. BorderFest celebrates the diverse cultures that make the [[Rio Grande Valley]] unique and is an opportunity to share, preserve and showcase South Texas heritage through education, music, dance, cultural activities, and family fun.<ref>[http://www.borderfest.org/history.html Welcome to BorderFest 2008! Celebrating China!<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060909101559/http://www.borderfest.org/history.html |date=September 9, 2006 }}</ref>
