The '''Festa de Nossa Senhora do Rosário'''  translates to [[Our Lady of the Rosary of Chiquinquirá|Festival of Our Lady of Rosário]]. It is the main celebration in the Brazilian city of [[Córrego Danta]]. '''Festa do Rosário''', a  celebration which involves almost all of the [[Catholicism|Catholic]] people in Córrego Danta, starts with a [[Catholic mass|mass]] in the main church and then a procession from the church to the Church of Our Lady of Rosary. Here is another celebration when the flag with an image of the saint is raised. It takes place in the city during the third weekend of August.

