{{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = Festum Ovorum |type = |image = |imagesize = |caption = |official_name = |nickname = |observedby = |litcolor = |longtype = |significance = |begins = |ends = |date = Saturday before Ash Wednesday |scheduling = |duration = 1 day |frequency = annual |celebrations = |observances = |relatedto = }} '''Egg Saturday''', '''Egg Feast''', or '''Festum Ovorum''' is the [[Saturday]] before [[Ash Wednesday]].<ref>Robert E. Brettle, [https://www.jstor.org/stable/507606 John Marston, Dramatist at Oxford, 1591 (?)–1594, 1609]. ''The Review of English Studies'', Volume 3, Number 12, pages 398–405, October 1927. [[Oxford University Press]]. [http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/59878#eid5774858 Oxford English Dictionary: Egg-Saturday]</ref>
At the [[University of Oxford]], [[pasch egg]]s have been provided for students on that day.{{fact|date=March 2010}}<ref>http://oxoniensia.org/volumes/1982/notes.pdf#page=4</ref>
