'''The Hamilton Circle Jerk''' is an annual music event in [[Hamilton, New Zealand]]. Named after a [[Non-penetrative sex|mutual masturbatory]] act, the Circle Jerk features 15 Hamilton bands performing 3 song sets, two songs by other Hamilton musicians as well as an original.
The first Circle Jerk was held in 2005. .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.3news.co.nz/Hamilton-hosts-its-6th-annual-Circle-Jerk-gig/tabid/418/articleID/158156/Default.aspx|title=Hamilton hosts its 6th annual Circle Jerk gig|work=3 News|date=28 May 2010|accessdate=15 September 2010}}</ref> Local student radio station [[Contact FM]] has been running the event since 2008.
==See also== *[[Hamilton, New Zealand]]
