{{Infobox music festival | name =International Computer Music Conference | image =Image:Hydraulophone performance at DGI-byen pool in Copenhagen.jpg | caption =The theme for ICMC 2007 was "Immersed Music". In keeping with this theme, there was an underwater [[hydraulophone]] performance at the DGI-byen swimcenter [[Vandkulturhuset]]. | location =Worldwide | years_active =1974-present | founders = | dates = | genre = [[Electronic music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website =[http://www.computermusic.org/ ICMA] }}
The '''International Computer Music Conference''' ('''ICMC''') is a yearly international conference for computer music researchers and composers. It is the annual conference of the [[International Computer Music Association]] (ICMA).
==History==
See the [http://www.computermusic.org/page/23/ CMA History Page] for a list.
In 1986, the [[Institute of Sonology]] institute was moved to the [[Royal Conservatory of The Hague]], hosting the International Computer Music Conference there during its inaugural year.<ref>Sani, N. and Bernardini, N. (1987), '1986 International Computer Music Conference, Den Haag: Review in Two Parts,' ''Perspectives of New Music'', 25 (1/2): 618-637</ref> Each year there is a specific theme. For example, in 2007, the theme was "Immersed Music" and immersive media. ICMC 2007 took place in Copenhagen. On Tuesday August 28, there was an "[http://www.icmc2007.net/?page_id=184 Underwater/Water Concert]" at the [[DGI-byen]] swimcenter, in the hundred-metre DGI-byen pool, as well as the various other pools of the [[Vandkulturhuset]].
This [http://www.aaue.dk/~niklas/ICMC/ "Immersed Music"] theme of ICMC 2007 explored important issues in [[Musical instrument classification#Physics-based classification scheme|musical instrument classification]] and immersion.
2014 40th ICMC is organised joint with the 11th [[Sound and Music Computing Conference]] in Athens, Greece 14–20 September 2014 [https://web.archive.org/web/20140224122305/http://www.icmc14-smc14.net/].
2018 44th ICMC took place from 5–10 August 2018 in Daegu, Korea. [https://icmc2018.org]
==See also== {{Commons category|International Computer Music Conference}} *[[List of electronic music festivals]]
